3) Why I choose CD 2 and reject CD 1
- Decisive positives for CD 2: The single strongest match to my current priorities is its remix‑minded design — concise 3–4‑minute club edits and the explicit availability of stems. Those attributes are central to “high‑energy, remix‑minded greatest‑hits treatments” I now prefer, because stems + club edits enable punchy reworkings and immediate DJ/producer use. The forward, multi‑tracked lead vocals with slapback align with my preference for close, present vocals (slapback preserves presence without heavy wash), and the emphasis on punchy transients and a locked low end supports the tactile midrange and headroom I value for rhythmic immediacy.
